dct_title_s: Map showing iron ranges and ore carrying railroads of Minnesota
dct_description_sm: Cartographic Details: Scale approximately 1:350,000 Inset shows generalized sections of Vermilion, Mesabi, Gogebic, Menominee, and Marquette Ranges. Includes distance tables for Duluth & Iron Range R.R., Duluth, Missabe & Northern Ry., and Great Northern Ry. "Mines shipping ore during season of 1906 are located on this map, also mines about to become shippers at date of this map. June 1907." Dimensions: 49 x 47 centimeters
dct_creator_sm: Oliver Iron Mining Company (Duluth, Minn.). Mining Engineering Department.
dct_publisher_sm: Oliver Iron Mining Co., Mining Engineering Dept.
